{"title":"Orto Estenosis Aórtica y Fractura de Cadera-2026","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Ortogeriatría/Orto Estenosis Aórtica y Fractura de Cadera-2026.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Estenosis Aórtica +\\NFractura de Cadera","guid":"dG4I-boLKEq_T3SrlSFWeg","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"¿Por qué es importante este tema?","guid":"3HGKJf7ELUy0Kng8VpSo9A","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"Problema frecuente: 3-8% de pacientes con Fx cadera tienen EA moderada/severa","guid":"iwgBPzG8IEW6CEtbmUb45w","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"Dilema clínico: la Fx cadera requiere cirugía urgente, pero la EA aumenta el riesgo quirúrgico","guid":"wqQtK3_JAEmBHxLjObcwCQ","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"Sin tratamiento de EA: mortalidad 1 año ~50%","guid":"2YFMKLU2h0OPz06_tQ7W8w","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"Con tratamiento adecuado: se puede reducir significativamente la mortalidad","guid":"Xq06X9AvAECU9kW-uCIezg","children":[]}]},{"id":"6","parent":"0","text":"¿Qué es la Estenosis\\NAórtica (EA)?","guid":"ZOr-eDwMHUijKfLoD04cEg","children":[{"id":"7","parent":"6","text":"Válvula aórtica engrosada y calcificada que no abre bien","guid":"ceWQboTTP02LOTnatPTQag","children":[]},{"id":"8","parent":"6","text":"Obstruye la salida de sangre del ventrículo izquierdo","guid":"7xfrRtzStESZDBFB0-FECw","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"6","text":"El corazón debe hacer más esfuerzo para bombear","guid":"axpWbcCbuU-OpYx_G6gVFg","children":[]},{"id":"10","parent":"6","text":"Progresiva: empeora con el tiempo si no se trata","guid":"s4EXn460h0CecGwp7ysfUg","children":[]}]},{"id":"11","parent":"0","text":"Conceptos\\NBásicos","guid":"d7Ne06Et-UuXWfRGY_q3mw","children":[{"id":"12","parent":"11","text":"Clasificación por Severidad\\N(Ecocardiograma)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"Leve: AVA >1.5 cm², Vmax <3 m/s, Gradiente medio <20 mmHg","guid":"fT503wXNLkeahTQfAi77Qg","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"Moderada: AVA 1.0-1.5 cm², Vmax 3-4 m/s, Gradiente 20-40 mmHg","guid":"1eDu9UR6ek25GDZe7woXNg","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"Severa: AVA <1.0 cm², Vmax >4 m/s, Gradiente >40 mmHg","guid":"tRlUYLIupUOs_LIo5YcaTA","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"Muy severa/crítica: AVA <0.75 cm², Vmax >5 m/s, Gradiente >60 mmHg","guid":"owZ61Nn2EkiXGLUB2NjtVA","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"11","text":"¿Por qué coexisten EA y\\NFractura de Cadera?","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"Paradoja de la\\NCalcificación","guid":"tGxG5l7mskyWcU6s0glUiA","children":[{"id":"19","parent":"18","text":"Mismo paciente tiene huesos débiles (osteoporosis) + válvula calcificada","guid":"HVyfxEPnykamL16Cl27JVw","children":[]},{"id":"20","parent":"18","text":"Mecanismo común: alteración del metabolismo calcio-fósforo","guid":"TOOU03GBSUKYQs17WhF44A","children":[]},{"id":"21","parent":"18","text":"El calcio \"sale\" del hueso y se \"deposita\" en tejidos blandos (válvulas, arterias)","guid":"fygfabeyvU6MczhaxZCIlQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"22","parent":"17","text":"Triada de Riesgo\\Nen el Adulto Mayor","guid":"51x6BXjrC02XJgY90z26fw","children":[{"id":"23","parent":"22","text":"EA severa → síncope/mareos → caídas → fractura de cadera","guid":"RRMXxrIECU-lB7Abnmg1ZQ","children":[]},{"id":"24","parent":"22","text":"Huesos frágiles por osteoporosis facilitan la fractura","guid":"Hy2CY1Mx-kSkJU0tmkFHXg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"25","parent":"11","text":"Síntomas Clásicos\\Nde EA (las 3 \"A\")","guid":"kPaFwKk9uGshj4n018oBnw","children":[{"id":"26","parent":"25","text":"Angina: dolor de pecho por mala perfusión coronaria","guid":"blvsjTrXIx2xHOXEFqx90Q","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"25","text":"Arritmias/síncope: pérdida de conciencia por bajo gasto cerebral","guid":"RDnByzAcHZmQ10mPnmQ-4Q","children":[]},{"id":"28","parent":"25","text":"Astenia/disnea: falta de aire por insuficiencia cardíaca","guid":"8EKZxj1dfijjl0QzRqdbOg","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"25","text":"PROBLEMA: muchos ancianos tienen síntomas \"enmascarados\" porque caminan poco","guid":"w5uqa-TAAOyEeAvNlDr-Gg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"30","parent":"0","text":"Estenosis Aórtica + Fractura de\\NCadera en el Adulto Mayor","guid":"_vcQf_H77kW9EHuVVXDVpw","children":[{"id":"31","parent":"30","text":"Fisiopatología: ¿Por qué la EA\\Nes tan peligrosa en cirugía?","guid":"mkNbs9_AMvO7cnjm6j5JUA","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"El Ventrículo Izquierdo\\Nen EA Severa","guid":"eFzsyuh0IdWYmdNeNf4ssw","children":[{"id":"33","parent":"32","text":"Se hipertrofia (engrosa) para vencer la obstrucción","guid":"Tc6eMp5R0aNpOWW3m3vkfw","children":[]},{"id":"34","parent":"32","text":"Se vuelve \"rígido\" y poco adaptable a cambios","guid":"Dd-d2g8mHcXQeDcQawgV-g","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"32","text":"Depende mucho de la contracción auricular (hasta 40% del llenado)","guid":"KBJWvaTgvkw843s9YlC56A","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"32","text":"Necesita presión arterial estable para perfundir sus propias coronarias","guid":"wEmfRAbBYBwRmnsHuqt8tQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"31","text":"¿Qué pasa durante la\\Nanestesia/cirugía?","guid":"","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"Vasodilatación → cae la presión arterial → mala perfusión coronaria","guid":"8xSN-OoLaEvdo7AswYrIsg","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"Sangrado → hipovolemia → bajo gasto cardíaco","guid":"EnNTqp9MHaXKhtwBhFGu_g","children":[]},{"id":"40","parent":"37","text":"Taquicardia → menos tiempo de llenado → menos gasto","guid":"3qq4SiACKxCauSeAdXQWSw","children":[]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"Fibrilación auricular → pérdida de la \"patada auricular\" → colapso","guid":"4_zy8oMnIo1uZYVuIppAjA","children":[]},{"id":"42","parent":"37","text":"Círculo vicioso: hipotensión → isquemia → peor función → más hipotensión","guid":"lyI9mMuN33pHFo-_4qiRZw","children":[]}]},{"id":"43","parent":"31","text":"Resultado sin\\Nintervención","guid":"GRn6aHZ9c3OV5JAjw8yYgg","children":[{"id":"44","parent":"43","text":"Mortalidad 30 días: 3-4 veces mayor que pacientes sin EA","guid":"FH5BjvWWHnOmwFUVMlo2zg","children":[]},{"id":"45","parent":"43","text":"IAM perioperatorio: 15.6% vs 1.1%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"43","text":"Mortalidad 1 año: 46% vs 18%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"47","parent":"30","text":"Evaluación\\Ndel Paciente","guid":"CaHils2bY6gRysP6tjIsEw","children":[{"id":"48","parent":"47","text":"Paso 1:\\NIdentificar la EA","guid":"ujloLgzkFfB-HVcUgjNcGg","children":[{"id":"49","parent":"48","text":"Auscultación: soplo sistólico eyectivo en foco aórtico, irradiado a carótidas","guid":"JImFszgbQwLwXtxxEVvCng","children":[]},{"id":"50","parent":"48","text":"Pulso: parvus et tardus (débil y retrasado)","guid":"d11iJoiE1UJordled3C73w","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"48","text":"Antecedentes: síncope, angina, disnea de esfuerzo, IC previa","guid":"kmXCv2jTpCL-USq9eyQayQ","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"48","text":"Ecocardiograma: confirma\\Ndiagnóstico y severidad","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"NO pedir de rutina en todos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"SÍ pedir si: soplo nuevo, sospecha valvulopatía, IC descompensada","guid":"3KmWf9qsg7_VBiKNEWz_jg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"55","parent":"47","text":"Paso 2: Determinar si\\Nes SINTOMÁTICA","guid":"","children":[{"id":"56","parent":"55","text":"Interrogar\\Nmecanismo\\Nde caída","guid":"Ps0VmPb4VdI591iHkbllhA","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"Caída mecánica (tropezó con objeto): probablemente asintomática","guid":"rViy-tgHlFY2C1KTXLpxmQ","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"Caída con pródromos (mareo, visión borrosa, \"se fue a negro\"): SINTOMÁTICA","guid":"nXquRwFkV15D7KwOZzVAUw","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"Caída con dolor torácico previo: SINTOMÁTICA","guid":"gDwzg-2GpzkZPU3NoUMZ_w","children":[]}]},{"id":"60","parent":"55","text":"Preguntar por\\Nsíntomas previos","guid":"yFiPNhLXf0GdJLjg5QgR7g","children":[{"id":"61","parent":"60","text":"¿Disnea al caminar? ¿Cuántas cuadras?","guid":"OcKK5nc70bev5W6mI4e81A","children":[]},{"id":"62","parent":"60","text":"¿Dolor de pecho con esfuerzo?","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"60","text":"¿Duerme con almohadas extra? (ortopnea)","guid":"ngkvomRLwgXg3nvY9UUxIw","children":[]},{"id":"64","parent":"60","text":"¿Se ha desmayado antes?","guid":"","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"65","parent":"47","text":"Paso 3: Evaluar Fragilidad (EFT -\\NEssential Frailty Toolset)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"66","parent":"65","text":"La fragilidad predice mala recuperación independiente de la EA","guid":"juXqjeqYwlC9wdY8amWU5Q","children":[]},{"id":"67","parent":"65","text":"4 componentes\\Nfáciles de evaluar","guid":"s8L-jQ9GM4pyvjvqCR12_Q","children":[{"id":"68","parent":"67","text":"Prueba de la silla: levantarse 5\\Nveces sin usar manos","guid":"","children":[{"id":"69","parent":"68","text":"<15 segundos = 0 puntos (normal)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"68","text":"≥15 segundos = 1 punto (lento)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"68","text":"No puede = 2 puntos (incapaz)","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"72","parent":"67","text":"Cognición: MMSE <24 = 1 punto","guid":"","children":[{"id":"73","parent":"72","text":"Atajo: si recuerda 3/3 palabras tras\\Ndistracción → muy probable MMSE ≥24","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"74","parent":"67","text":"Hemoglobina: <13 g/dL (hombre) o <12 g/dL (mujer) = 1 punto","guid":"LCvg1YLRWfONvlz2G-I8yA","children":[]},{"id":"75","parent":"67","text":"Albúmina: <3.5 g/dL = 1 punto","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"76","parent":"65","text":"Interpretación\\N(puntuación 0-5)","guid":"AiGo23PoGXs6Xz2EPNfYwA","children":[{"id":"77","parent":"76","text":"0-1: bajo riesgo, buena recuperación esperada","guid":"VTqcYrSPI2PuGlTVOHbmIg","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"76","text":"2: riesgo moderado","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"76","text":"3: riesgo alto","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"80","parent":"76","text":"4-5: riesgo muy alto, considerar futilidad (80% malos resultados con 5/5)","guid":"ot_FY9CTZVhkT6CcqgMbsA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"81","parent":"47","text":"Paso 4: Estratificar\\NRiesgo Cardíaco (RCRI)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"1 punto por cada\\Nfactor presente","guid":"6FPSmVSgeoW9mzZLG_Pbtg","children":[{"id":"83","parent":"82","text":"Cirugía de alto riesgo (Fx cadera = SÍ)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"82","text":"Cardiopatía isquémica previa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"82","text":"Insuficiencia cardíaca previa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"86","parent":"82","text":"ACV/TIA previo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"87","parent":"82","text":"Diabetes con insulina","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"82","text":"Creatinina >2 mg/dL","guid":"","children":[]}]},{"id":"89","parent":"81","text":"Riesgo de eventos cardíacos\\Nmayores a 30 días","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"0 puntos: 3.9%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"1 punto: 6%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"2 puntos: 10.1%","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"93","parent":"89","text":"≥3 puntos: 15%","guid":"","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"94","parent":"30","text":"Algoritmo de Manejo\\Nsegún Escenario Clínico","guid":"","children":[{"id":"95","parent":"94","text":"GRUPO 0: EA Severa\\NAsintomática (caída mecánica)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"Perfil del\\Npaciente","guid":"LGM7YFY7RvprgXqevOEzQg","children":[{"id":"97","parent":"96","text":"Caída por tropiezo claro (manguera, escalón)","guid":"UlLBwMjBaWGx4c8nmq3giQ","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"96","text":"Niega síncope, angina, disnea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"99","parent":"96","text":"Ecocardiograma: AVA ~0.9-1.0 cm², FEVI >50%, gradiente <50 mmHg","guid":"r8k19CKXy7VtKP4Fx3lY2Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"100","parent":"95","text":"Conducta","guid":"","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"Cirugía de cadera directa dentro de 24 horas","guid":"bTZ_7h7EHEb-T6uTwQEsjg","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"Monitoreo hemodinámico invasivo (línea arterial, considerar Swan-Ganz)","guid":"QlpBElq35cuClxkTdoUZdA","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"Metas estrictas: FC 70-90, mantener precarga, NO dejar caer presión","guid":"gAnz7nG5Uco_c8fVGmPc_Q","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"100","text":"Seguimiento cardiológico ambulatorio post-alta para planificar intervención valvular electiva","guid":"x6hQH_oJSbauGye4qA-p7w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"94","text":"GRUPO 1: EA Severa Sintomática + TAVI\\NFactible Mínimamente Invasiva","guid":"","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"Perfil del\\Npaciente","guid":"Ie8XxMDNQHD9klj2rMIx1Q","children":[{"id":"107","parent":"106","text":"Síncope, angina o disnea previo a caída","guid":"RN7NCoyTZpn-39y_QTC7JQ","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"106","text":"Ecocardiograma: AVA <0.8 cm², FEVI puede estar reducida","guid":"aho7fsQAL-hdXaQmdKSa5w","children":[]},{"id":"109","parent":"106","text":"Anatomía favorable: acceso femoral posible, senos de Valsalva adecuados","guid":"pWJLGO4ZcQA3mPdud-SaeA","children":[]},{"id":"110","parent":"106","text":"Sin contraindicaciones para TAVI de urgencia","guid":"2VkOYG9MhoUHMG5KXCmcsg","children":[]}]},{"id":"111","parent":"105","text":"Conducta\\N(secuencia ideal)","guid":"Z5N1bulI-87kxS6Qp_xefw","children":[{"id":"112","parent":"111","text":"TAVI mínimamente invasiva primero (sedación + anestesia local)","guid":"SleHzwPuWbTDON-ru5GOxQ","children":[]},{"id":"113","parent":"111","text":"Recuperación fast-track (6-12 horas)","guid":"kJC4qjUY308PsZGX-LncaA","children":[]},{"id":"114","p